== Basmati Rice ==

Boil a half-full #kettle{}. Pour the boiled water into a large #saucepan{} with @salt{1/4%tsp} on high heat. Add the @Basmati Rice{150%g} and cook for ~{10-12%mins}.

Once cooked, drain in a #sieve{} and pop back in the pan. Cover with a #lid{} and leave to the side until ready to serve.

== Devilled Paneer ==

Meanwhile, cut the @Paneer{226%g} into 1cm cubes. Chop half the @Red Onion{1/2}(chopped into 2cm chunks) and thinly slice the other half.

Heat the @Oil for Cooking{1%tbsp} in a #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the paneer and onion chunks to the pan. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Fry until golden all over, ~{5-8%mins}. Turn regularly to brown the paneer evenly.

Once the paneer is cooked, stir in the @Ginger Puree{15%g}, @Tomato Puree{30%g} and @Ground Cinnamon{1%sachet}. Fry until fragrant, ~{1%min}.

Mix in the @Soy Sauce{25%ml}, @Tomato Ketchup{1%tbsp}, @Sugar for the Sauce{2%tsp} and @Water for the Sauce{75%ml}. Bring to a boil, then reduce the heat and simmer until thickened, ~{3-4%mins}.

Stir the @Hot Sauce{30%g} into the paneer. Add a splash of water if it's a little too thick.

Taste and season with more @salt{}, @pepper{} and @sugar{} if needed.

== Mango Sambol ==

Peel the @Mango{1}(peeled). Slice down either side of the stone to make 2 'cheeks'. Cut any remaining flesh from the stone, then cut the mango into 1cm thin slices (discard the stone).

Cut the @Lime{1} into wedges.

In a #medium bowl{}, combine the juice from the lime with the @Sugar for the Pickle{1%tsp}.

Toss the sliced red onion through the lime dressing. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Gently stir in the mango and set aside for later.

== To Serve ==

Share the rice between your #bowls{}.

Top with the devilled paneer and mango sambol in separate sections.

Enjoy!

> The 'devilled' sauce is a common sauce in Sri Lankan cuisine, an acidic hot sauce that's tomato based with spices and can be served with any proteins. Here, we've chosen paneer to soak up all the flavour!

> Sambol is a variant of salsa or chutney that's typically used as a topping or side in Sri Lankan cuisine, often being served with every dish.